The paper discusses a machine learning approach for online learning tasks, specifically in the context of recommendation and binary classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithmic framework for online learning, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on recommendation tasks suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), while the use of optimization techniques could place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
